谢谢你,先生

1169
01:31:02,588 --> 01:31:06,008
Are you all right? Thank you.

1170
01:31:08,144 --> 01:31:11,238
你真好心,肯帮助我
You're such a gentleman.
It's so kind of you to help me.

1171
01:31:10,888 --> 01:31:14,892
I really wasn't sure
if we'd make it or not.

1172
01:31:11,848 --> 01:31:14,146
我担心自己是否能办到

1173
01:31:18,722 --> 01:31:22,749
- 有问题吗?我来帮你
- 不用
Is there some problem
I can help you with?

1174
01:31:21,690 --> 01:31:25,777
- No.
- I really can't thank you enough.

1175
01:31:23,059 --> 01:31:26,324
我真的很感谢你

1176
01:31:30,467 --> 01:31:34,665
你真可爱
Isn't this fun? You're being
such a good boy, sweetheart.

1177
01:31:36,272 --> 01:31:38,797
你真好,真谢谢你
Thank you again,
this is so wonderful.

1178
01:31:41,376 --> 01:31:43,504
Thank you, sir.

1179
01:31:52,522 --> 01:31:59,018
我来吧,先生,谢谢你帮忙
Please, let me take it from here.
You've been such a great help.

1180
01:31:56,016 --> 01:31:59,102
Thank you so much.
We're almost there.

1181
01:32:01,271 --> 01:32:06,735
I'll take it from here, sir.
Thank you very much for your help.

1182
01:32:08,904 --> 01:32:12,533
Don't cry, sweetheart.
We're almost home.

1183
01:32:09,472 --> 01:32:12,839
别哭,宝宝,我们快到家了

1184
01:32:14,144 --> 01:32:18,444
有什么不对吗?先生
Is something wrong?

1185
01:32:17,204 --> 01:32:18,539
Sir?

1186
01:34:14,764 --> 01:34:16,823
快点!离开这里
Come on!
Come on, let's get out of here.

1187
01:34:17,824 --> 01:34:21,370
- What are you doin'?
- Shut up!

1188
01:34:18,668 --> 01:34:21,603
- 你干什么?
- 闭嘴,走

1189
01:34:25,008 --> 01:34:26,908
闭嘴
- What are you doin'?
- Shut the fuck up!

1190
01:34:27,110 --> 01:34:29,044
别动

1191
01:34:27,626 --> 01:34:30,963
- Hold it!
- Please...

1192
01:34:29,779 --> 01:34:31,440
别动

1193
01:34:31,171 --> 01:34:33,799
- My baby!
- Stay there. He's all right.

1194
01:34:31,714 --> 01:34:34,342
- 我的宝宝
- 别动,他没事

1195
01:34:36,686 --> 01:34:38,244
我说别动
I said hold it!

1196
01:34:40,123 --> 01:34:42,614
我要和簿记员一起走出去
I'm walkin' out with the bookkeeper.

1197
01:34:42,826 --> 01:34:46,023
簿记员将和我驾车离开
The bookkeeper and me
are drivin' away.

1198
01:34:48,531 --> 01:34:53,935
如果他死了,你们就什么都没了
See? Or else he dies.

1199
01:34:50,524 --> 01:34:53,569
He dies, and you ain't got nothin'.

1200
01:34:56,989 --> 01:35:00,200
You got five seconds
to make up your mind.

1201
01:34:57,507 --> 01:35:00,442
给你们五秒钟决定

1202
01:35:01,177 --> 01:35:03,805
我告诉你们…我告诉你们所想知道的一切
- I'll tell ya what ya want to know!
- Shut up! I'm not kiddin'!

1203
01:35:04,013 --> 01:35:05,241
闭嘴

1204
01:35:05,448 --> 01:35:06,437
我不是说着玩

1205
01:35:06,649 --> 01:35:10,312
杀了他,我什么都告诉你们
He's crazy! Don't let him do this,
I'll tell you what you want to know!

1206
01:35:10,920 --> 01:35:12,148
你瞄准他了
- You got him?
- Yeah, I got him.

1207
01:35:12,455 --> 01:35:13,854
是的,我瞄准了

1208
01:35:18,728 --> 01:35:20,025
一
- One!
- Will you stop it!

1209
01:35:20,230 --> 01:35:21,492
请你们制止他

1210
01:35:27,170 --> 01:35:28,432
解决他
Take him.

1211
01:35:30,940 --> 01:35:32,066
二
Two.

1212
01:35:59,120 --> 01:36:04,524
这帐本上的记号代表了收付对象
The two coded entries
in this ledger

1213
01:36:02,095 --> 01:36:06,767
represent cash disbursement
to all levels of city officials,

1214
01:36:04,725 --> 01:36:08,752
包括了各级政府官员、警察人员

1215
01:36:06,975 --> 01:36:12,648
members of the police
and to Alphonse Capone.

1216
01:36:08,996 --> 01:36:12,693
还有艾尔卡彭,是不是

1217
01:36:14,635 --> 01:36:16,102
没错
- That's correct.
- Excuse me?

1218
01:36:16,303 --> 01:36:17,395
你说什么

1219
01:36:19,073 --> 01:36:20,973
你说得没错
I said that is correct.

1220
01:36:21,709 --> 01:36:26,305
而你会替我们译出帐本上的代号
And you will decipher
these coded entries for us?

1221
01:36:28,716 --> 01:36:30,650
是的
I will.

1222
01:36:30,918 --> 01:36:33,250
对不起,佩恩先生,我听不到
Sorry, Mr. Payne, I can't hear you.

1223
01:36:33,687 --> 01:36:35,348
是的,我会
I said, I will.

1224
01:36:36,690 --> 01:36:40,285
你负责替卡彭先生管帐
You were in charge
of disbursements for Mr. Capone?

1225
01:36:41,595 --> 01:36:42,823
是的
Yes, I was.

1226
01:36:43,063 --> 01:36:52,335
而你是亲自将那些
未报税的巨款交给卡彭先生
And you personally
distributed monies...

1227
01:36:46,139 --> 01:36:50,185
...vast, undeclared monies...

1228
01:36:50,394 --> 01:36:53,730
...to Mr. Capone?

1229
01:36:54,008 --> 01:36:55,134
是的
Yes, I did.

1230
01:36:56,610 --> 01:36:59,044
你能告诉我们总数吗?
Would you tell us the amounts?

1231
01:37:01,115 --> 01:37:02,912
三年来
In a three-year period I personally
disbursed monies to Mr. Capone

1232
01:37:03,117 --> 01:37:11,718
我亲自交给卡彭先生一百三十多万元

1233
01:37:07,160 --> 01:37:12,040
in excess of one
and a third million dollars.

1234
01:37:15,129 --> 01:37:17,893
请你再重复一次
Would you repeat that amount, please?

1235
01:37:18,966 --> 01:37:22,129
一百三十万美元
- One and a third million dollars.
- Thank you very much.

1236
01:37:22,336 --> 01:37:24,770
谢谢你

1237
01:37:40,254 --> 01:37:43,314
我不明白,卡彭为何有恃无恐
I don't understand it.
What does Capone have?

1238
01:37:43,524 --> 01:37:46,220
他一直在微笑
We're nailing the lid on his coffin,
and he's smiling.

1239
01:38:10,885 --> 01:38:12,944
那家伙在法庭上带枪
The son-of-a-bitch
is wearing a gun in court.

1240
01:38:17,191 --> 01:38:18,488
叫法警来
Get me the bailiff.

1241
01:38:21,295 --> 01:38:23,695
很快会结束的
It'll be a fast trial.

1242
01:38:26,433 --> 01:38:30,699
那个穿白西装的人身上带了把枪
The man in the front row wearing
a white suit is carrying a gun.

1243
01:38:31,071 --> 01:38:34,940
我不希望在此闹事,你叫他出去
I don't want this to turn
into something. I'll lead you out.

1244
01:38:34,941 --> 01:38:36,468
是,先生

1245
01:38:43,150 --> 01:38:45,175
请你出来一下好吗
Could we speak to you
a minute, please?

1246
01:39:14,114 --> 01:39:15,741
- 面对墙壁
- 你以为你是谁?
- Get up against it.
- You heard him. Now, up against it!

1247
01:39:15,950 --> 01:39:18,009
你听到他的话了

1248
01:39:20,043 --> 01:39:23,797
- What's this?
- Empty all your pockets, all of it.

1249
01:39:21,588 --> 01:39:24,318
好了,把口袋掏空放在这里,全拿出来

1250
01:39:24,006 --> 01:39:27,634
- I've got a permit for that.
- Fine, let's see it.

1251
01:39:24,525 --> 01:39:27,255
- 我有带枪的许可
- 我看看

1252
01:39:31,198 --> 01:39:33,063
遭起诉的人不是我
- I'm not the one under indictment.
- Everything on the table.

1253
01:39:33,267 --> 01:39:34,666
把东西放在桌上

1254
01:39:38,187 --> 01:39:40,397
- Let me see.
- Give him his gun back.

1255
01:39:39,840 --> 01:39:40,864
把枪还他

1256
01:39:41,075 --> 01:39:47,036
请给予弗兰克尼蒂先生一切的方便和工作
"To Whom It May Concern.
Please extend to the bearer,"

1257
01:39:43,066 --> 01:39:46,945
"Mr. Frank Nitti, all possible
courtesy and consideration."

1258
01:39:47,247 --> 01:39:49,442
威廉汤姆森,芝加哥市长
"William Thompson,
Mayor of the City of Chicago."

1259
01:39:49,650 --> 01:39:52,118
对不起,奈斯先生,你必须把枪还他
I'm sorry, Mr. Ness,
you'll have to give it back.

1260
01:39:53,487 --> 01:39:58,948
好吧,但那家伙不准再进入法庭,你明白吗
Fine. But that man does not go
back into that courtroom.

1261
01:39:57,623 --> 01:40:00,792
- Do you understand me?
- Yes, sir.

1262
01:39:59,159 --> 01:40:00,319
是的,长官

1263
01:40:26,320 --> 01:40:28,584
“拉辛路1634号”

1264
01:40:31,158 --> 01:40:36,960
拉辛路1634号,我曾有位朋友住在那里
1634 Racine... You know, I used
to have a friend who lived there.

1265
01:40:50,544 --> 01:40:53,638
不要,让他走
Don't. Let him go.

1266
01:40:56,850 --> 01:40:58,181
不要
- No!
- Here, take it.

1267
01:45:10,437 --> 01:45:12,268
我在这里,财政官员
Here I am, Treasury Man.
Come on! Harass me!

1268
01:45:12,973 --> 01:45:15,908
来呀,逮捕我

1269
01:45:17,311 --> 01:45:23,113
你在等什么,别光站在那里,逮捕我呀
What are you waitin' for?

1270
01:45:20,320 --> 01:45:23,323
Don't just stand there!
Harass me!

1271
01:45:27,721 --> 01:45:29,313
别惹火了我
Don't push me.

1272
01:45:32,392 --> 01:45:34,053
我要送你下地狱,老兄
- They're gonna burn you, buddy.
- Yeah?

1273
01:45:34,261 --> 01:45:35,285
是吗

1274
01:45:35,495 --> 01:45:40,432
没错,我要看你下狱,因为你杀了我朋友
Yeah. I'm gonna come see you burn,
you son-of-a-bitch!

1275
01:45:38,714 --> 01:45:40,883
'Cause you killed my friend!

1276
01:45:41,134 --> 01:45:43,261
他死得像只猪一样
- He died like a pig.
- What did you say?

1277
01:45:43,870 --> 01:45:44,928
你说什么

1278
01:45:45,138 --> 01:45:48,835
我说你朋友死前哀号得像猪一样
I said that your friend died
screaming like a stuck Irish pig.

1279
01:45:49,042 --> 01:45:51,704
等我脱罪时,你慢慢想吧
Now you think about that
when I beat the rap.

1280
01:46:06,159 --> 01:46:08,150
像你这样吗?
Did he sound anything like that?

1281
01:46:39,092 --> 01:46:40,992
拍张照,拍张照
One picture, come on, one picture.

1282
01:46:44,531 --> 01:46:46,590
奈斯,看看这个
Mr. Ness, take a look at this.

1283
01:46:48,869 --> 01:46:50,496
奈斯先生
Mr. Ness?

1284
01:46:52,272 --> 01:46:53,933
奈斯先生,你还好吧?
Mr. Ness, are you doin' okay?
I think you'd better see this.

1285
01:46:54,474 --> 01:46:55,964
你最好看看这个

1286
01:46:57,477 --> 01:46:58,671
这是什么
- What is it?
- That's the jury list, Mr. Ness.

1287
01:46:58,879 --> 01:47:01,677
这是陪审团名单,他们被收买了

1288
01:47:00,671 --> 01:47:02,464
They've been bribed.

1289
01:47:02,816 --> 01:47:04,579
从尼蒂西装里搜出来的
I got it out of Nitti's coat.
Where is Nitti?

1290
01:47:05,352 --> 01:47:06,683
尼蒂呢?

1291
01:47:08,588 --> 01:47:09,885
他在车上
He's in the car.

1292
01:47:29,443 --> 01:47:32,708
这不构成证据,没有用
This constitutes no evidence.
I'm not about to allow...

1293
01:47:32,913 --> 01:47:33,845
我可不准许

1294
01:47:33,537 --> 01:47:39,251
Your Honor, the truth is that Capone
is a killer and he will go free.

1295
01:47:34,047 --> 01:47:36,743
庭上,这案子的事实是,
卡彭是个杀人凶手

1296
01:47:36,950 --> 01:47:38,508
而你却要让他自由

1297
01:47:39,619 --> 01:47:43,146
对付他这种人只有一种办法,
便是把他关起来
There is only one way to deal with
such men, and that is hunt them down.

1298
01:47:44,891 --> 01:47:49,055
我曾发誓,我要不计任何方法捉住被告
I have. I have forsworn myself.
I have broken laws I swore to defend.

1299
01:47:49,262 --> 01:47:51,628
我很满意我所做的正确方法
I am content that I have done right.
That man must be stopped, you must...

1300
01:47:51,832 --> 01:47:53,527
那个人必须被制止,而你一定要…

1301
01:47:53,733 --> 01:47:57,328
我是法官,我会尽我的责任,奈斯先生
I'll be the judge
of what I must do, Mr. Ness.

1302
01:48:07,481 --> 01:48:08,812
请你们出去好吗
Would you excuse us?

1303
01:49:12,112 --> 01:49:13,602
- 法警
- 是的
- Bailiff.
- Yes, sir.

1304
01:49:18,718 --> 01:49:20,879
我要你去隔壁霍法官的法庭
I want you to go next door
to Judge Hoffman's Court,

1305
01:49:21,087 --> 01:49:23,715
他们刚开始审理离婚案件
where they've just begun hearing
a divorce action.

1306
01:49:24,457 --> 01:49:27,426
我要你把他的陪审团带来
I want you to bring that jury in here
and take this jury to his court.

1307
01:49:27,627 --> 01:49:30,323
把这里的陪审团带过去

1308
01:49:32,065 --> 01:49:33,589
你听清楚了吗
- Are those instructions clear?
- Yes, sir, they're clear.

1309
01:49:33,800 --> 01:49:35,597
是的,庭上

1310
01:49:36,570 --> 01:49:38,561
他说什么
What's he talking about?

1311
01:49:40,173 --> 01:49:44,473
- 我要你调换陪审团
- 是的
Bailiff, I want you
to switch the juries.

1312
01:49:44,678 --> 01:49:45,975
我抗议
Your Honor, I object!

1313
01:49:47,447 --> 01:49:48,675
驳回
Overruled.

1314
01:49:53,219 --> 01:49:55,210
你是怎么说动他的
What did you tell him?

1315
01:49:57,057 --> 01:49:59,287
我说他的名字也在帐本上
I told him his name was
in the ledger, too.

1316
01:50:01,561 --> 01:50:03,188
但他的名字并不在帐本上
His name wasn't in the ledger!

1317
01:50:04,564 --> 01:50:07,431
怎么回事
Wait a second! Is this the law?
What's goin' on here?

1318
01:50:07,634 --> 01:50:09,124
请守秩序
- You're out of order.
- What's goin' on?

1319
01:50:09,336 --> 01:50:10,234
我认为
- I think...
- Do somethin' here.

1320
01:50:10,437 --> 01:50:12,132
我不管你认为什么,想点办法

1321
01:50:12,973 --> 01:50:15,840
我看起来像什么?想点办法呀
What do I look like to you?
Do somethin'!

1322
01:50:16,042 --> 01:50:17,407
秩序
Order!

1323
01:50:19,312 --> 01:50:25,308
庭上,我们撤回无罪申辩,改为有罪申辩
Your Honor, we'd like to withdraw
our plea of Not Guilty,

1324
01:50:23,540 --> 01:50:25,501
and enter a plea of Guilty.

1325
01:50:29,087 --> 01:50:31,882
- Guilty?
- Order in the court!

1326
01:50:30,557 --> 01:50:33,492
维持庭上秩序,秩序

1327
01:50:32,090 --> 01:50:34,134
Order!

1328
01:50:42,936 --> 01:50:47,930
法警,维持秩序
Bailiff! Bailiff!

1329
01:50:46,146 --> 01:50:48,607
Bailiff, clear the courtroom!

1330
01:50:50,108 --> 01:50:51,443
Eliot!

1331
01:50:52,078 --> 01:50:55,138
庭上,庭上,这公正吗
Your Honor!
Is that justice?

1332
01:50:55,348 --> 01:50:57,816
他为何调换陪审团?
Please, why did he switch the jury?

1333
01:50:58,118 --> 01:51:00,780
你有何打算?你打算继续
Are you gonna go
after the organization?

1334
01:51:00,781 --> 01:51:02,153
借光
Excuse me.

1335
01:51:03,455 --> 01:51:06,750
I'm askin' Your Honor,
is this justice?

1336
01:51:06,893 --> 01:51:08,884
那是公正吗?

1337
01:51:11,464 --> 01:51:13,523
这样公正吗
Is this justice?

1338
01:51:17,370 --> 01:51:20,339
绝不停止,绝不停止战斗,直到战斗终止
Never stop fighting
till the fight is done.

1339
01:51:20,540 --> 01:51:21,837
你说什么
What did you say?

1340
01:51:22,175 --> 01:51:25,440
我说绝不停止战斗,直到战斗停止为止
I said, never stop fighting
till the fight is done.

1341
01:51:25,143 --> 01:51:27,187
- What?
- You heard me, Capone. It's over.

1342
01:51:25,745 --> 01:51:27,713
你听到我的话了,卡彭,都结束了

1343
01:51:27,396 --> 01:51:29,940
You're nothin'
but a lot of talk and a badge.

1344
01:51:27,914 --> 01:51:30,115
滚开,你只会说大话

1345
01:51:30,116 --> 01:51:33,051
最后一课
Here endeth the lesson.

1346
01:51:33,253 --> 01:51:35,278
你只知道口出狂言
You're nothin'
but a lot of talk and a badge!

1347
01:51:37,614 --> 01:51:40,826
You're nothin'
but a lot of talk and a badge!

1348
01:51:57,310 --> 01:51:59,835
“不可动摇者打击罪犯”

1349
01:52:02,582 --> 01:52:04,914
“奈斯保证不被收买”

1350
01:52:06,119 --> 01:52:08,110
“卡彭今天出庭”

1351
01:52:09,255 --> 01:52:13,589
“卡彭被判十一年徒刑”

1352
01:52:59,205 --> 01:53:00,695
太多暴力了
So much violence.

1353
01:54:07,607 --> 01:54:08,904
总算清理了一点
Cleaning up a little.

1354
01:54:18,551 --> 01:54:20,951
我想该说再见了
I guess this is goodbye.

1355
01:54:23,056 --> 01:54:24,387
再见,乔治
Goodbye, George.

1356
01:54:27,227 --> 01:54:28,785
我要感谢你
I want to... thank you for this.

1357
01:54:31,264 --> 01:54:33,528
不,谢谢你
No. Thank you.

1358
